    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The overall credibility assessment for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw FEA model under ASTM F1717 compression-bending is Accepted at Medium assurance level. Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels. The single shortfall in Test conditions (achieved gradation 2 vs. required gradation 3) is accepted on the basis that the F1717 protocol is a standardized single-condition test and the regulatory submission does not require multi-condition extrapolation. The assessment team formally accepts the residual risk associated with this gap. The model is suitable to support the Class II pre-market submission for the intended spinal fusion application.",
